{
  "stem": "365.4",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I gathered that he must have committed some crime, some murders in the home, [BACKROUND NOISE] the Polish town where he was.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because he mentioned the town's name and he mentioned just once, even about the Jewish wine that he drank on Passover.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he says they called it [NON-ENGLISH]-- that that goy-- and he used the term goy-- should not even look at it, because then it's no more Kosher.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even I didn't know those things at that time, when he explained to me.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He mentioned the town, Grodno, which was a famous town in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember reading a Polish author, a woman, describing a Jewish family in Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was one of the few that were friendly toward Jews-- describing a rabbinical family of Grodno.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Well, we worked there till-- we could see the newspapers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so when the Germans were reading them-- like that particular fellow used to push the newspaper like towards me so that I could see the headlines or read that they were already on the outskirts of Berlin then.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then work stopped all at once.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were just greasing all the machines, dismantling them, building them on trucks, take them on the train station, loading them on train cars to be shipped off, putting on the pilings on top, ripping them up.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they remained there till the Russians came in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We stopped a few days before the [BACKROUND NOISE] end of the war, which was already beginning of May.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember the last Saturday of the war, which happened to be May the 5th, we were sent to work-- a group of us-- to a sawmill, sorting some lumber things.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we finished in the early afternoon, about 2 o'clock.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
